    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-07-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-07-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="837"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d837">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to <persName
                            type="to">Mavroyeni Bey</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-07-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 95.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 11th instant, embodying the reply of Tevfik Pasha to mine of
                    May 29 last, regarding the destruction of American property at Harpoot and the
                    conduct of the Turkish authorities in connection therewith.</p>
                <p>I have sent a copy of your note to Minister Terrell at Constantinople with an
                    appropriate instruction.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
